A formal theory of computability, providing a systematic answer to the question "what (and how) can be computed?". Formulas represent interactive computational problems, and validity means being "always computable". Introduced by [http://www.csc.villanova.edu/~japaridz Japaridze] in 2003. External web source: [http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~giorgi/cl.html Computability Logic].